    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-28T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-28T22:00:00-05:00" n="687"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/10–1848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in France</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-28T22:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 28, 1948—10 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4208. For Harriman from State and <gloss target="#t_ECA1">ECA</gloss>.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d687fn1">Repeated to London for Douglas and Finletter as
                        4127.</note> Bonesteel<note n="2" xml:id="d687fn2">Lt. Col. Charles H.
                        Bonesteel, 3d, Executive Director of the European Coordinating Committee of
                        the Defense Assistance Program.</note> refers to recent approaches by
                    Hall-Patch to Harriman and by Makins to Finletter on problem of correlation
                    Western Union rearmament with <gloss target="#t_ERP1">ERP</gloss> (Dept of Army
                    tel <gloss target="#t_MA1">MA</gloss>659 from Paris Oct. 18<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d687fn3">Not printed.</note>). Only report on economic impact of
                    rearmament received here is account of discussion of Brit rearmament program
                    with Plowden<note n="4" xml:id="d687fn4">Sir Edwin Noel Plowden, Chief Planning
                        Officer and Chairman of the British Economic Planning Board.</note> by
                    Douglas and Finletter (London <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 4315
                    Sept 29<note n="3" xml:id="d687fn5">Not printed.</note>). Current Brit thinking
                    on this subject and your views would be helpful in our consideration of
                    problem.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
